text: That is a weird card
That's in the Savage Aura's Planechase deck.
Still think I'd rather just run O-Ring or one of the variants

It promotes a weird play state - no one else cares about it. If you enchant someone else's item they're nervous but who wants to waste enchantment removal on it? So if you want a bit of a hostage effect that also gives you Oloro.
If you enchant your own thing you just get the Oloro effect.
dont get me wrong there are plenty of cards that are better than this. however, i'm always looking to replace non-enchantment based effects with enchantment-based ones. gotta go deep sometimes
It isn't really like O-Ring or the like.
It's way worse :slightly_smiling_face:
Like I said.
Maybe if you were already packing Dowsing Shaman, Silent Sentinal, Skull of Orm, etc
If it was white it would have some recursion synergy with Hanna I guess

Even in Selesnya if you want enchantment-based removal you've got Soul Snare, O-Ring, Banishing Light, new cycling O-Ring whose name I can't remember, all the arrest effects, Song of the Dryads, Lignify, Seals of Cleansing/Primordium just off the top of my head. Not sure you need to dig that deep.
